You can change your algorithm to divide by `i` instead of multiplying by `i` so that the highest number will always be the input.  This will allow `Integer.MAX_VALUE` to function without changing the datatype:

    public static int solution(int N) {
        int count = 0;
        for (int i = 1; (N / i) &gt;= i; i++) {
            if (N / i == i) {
                count++;
                return count;
            }
            if (N % i == 0) {
                count += 2;
            }
        }
        return count;
    }

Note the `for` condition and first `if` conditions are now `(N / i) &gt;= i` and `N / i == i` which will have the same functionality as before.

